radiographic_examinations.findings: Moderate dependent atelectasis at the lung bases, with no consolidation or pleural effusion. Tiny focal hypodensity in the posterior right lobe of the liver, otherwise unremarkable abdominal organs. Distended appendix up to 11 mm with surrounding inflammatory change and small amount of pericecal fluid. No evidence of perforation or abscess. Physiologic amount of fluid in the cul-de-sac. No fractures or worrisome bony lesions.
